<TITLE>Feb 9 7:30pm International Piano Festival: Abbey Simon Recital</TITLE>
<TEXT>Works to be performed include: Mozart: Sonata in F major, K. 332; Beethoven: Sonata No. 31 in A-flat Major, Op. 110; Ravel: Valse nobles et sentimentales; Chopin: Four Impromptus, Op. 29, 36, 51, 66 
 
About the Performers 
 
Simon, a distinguished pianist and nonagenarian, returns to the stage for his first performance following a hiatus due to a terrible car accident. Debargue, the French pianist who stirred audiences and critics during the 2015 International Tchaikovsky Competition, has been praised for his incredible gift, artistic vision, and creative freedom. Driver, one of Britains most respected and versatile pianists, has earned numerous awards during his career and has been applauded for his impeccable technique and musicianship. American pianist Schein, internationally recognized as a leader in the field, will present a poetic recital for the festival that will demonstrate her unique grasp of style, her technical fluency, [and] her ability to make a melody sing out. 
 
To learn more about the International Piano Festival, please visit http://www.uh.edu/cota/music/events-performances/piano-festival/ 
 
Ticket and Parking Information 
 
Recitals will be performed in the Moores Opera House and master classes will be held in UHs Dudley Recital Hall. Free Arts Parking is available. Festival tickets can be purchased online at http://www.uh.edu/cota/music/events-performances/piano-festival/ticket-info/ or reserved by calling 713-743-3313. Prices are as follows: 
 4 Recital ONLY Package - $80, $46 for students and seniors  4 Recitals and master classes - $112, $65 for students and seniors  Single recitals - $25, $15 for students and seniors  Single master classes - $10, $5 for students and seniors  Artist conversation luncheon - $20 (includes boxed lunch)</TEXT>
